In this example directory is all the code for a simple worker with 
an ajax progress bar.

First create an empty rails application.
  rails progressbar_demo
  cd progressbar_demo

Second: install a clean version of backgrounddrb.
  cd vendor/plugins
  svn co http://svn.devjavu.com/backgroundrb/tags/release-0.2.1 backgroundrb
  cd ../../
  rake backgroundrb:setup

Copy the following files to the appropriate directory within your Rails app.
  drb_controller.rb => app/controllers dir
  drb/ => app/views/ dir
  drb.css => public/stylesheets
  drb.js => public/javascripts
  progress_worker.rb => lib/workers

Next, run the app.
  script/backgroundrb start
  script/server start
  
View the magic at:
  http://localhost:3000/drb
  
When you feel up to some higher level backgroundrb magic, it is a good idea to stop the current app.
  script/server stop
  script/backgroundrb stop
  
 